Text.SourceString: My day is going great, thank you for asking, <PlayerName>$player</>. How are you today?//<portrait=happy>Have you checked out my furniture store?
Text.LocalizedString: My day is going great, thank you for asking, <PlayerName>$player</>. How are you today?//<portrait=happy>Have you checked out my furniture store?

Text.SourceString: No time like the present, I always say. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: No time like the present, I always say. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: I’m not one for gardening, but it would be nice to rely less on <NpcName>Sam</> for fresh fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not one for gardening, but it would be nice to rely less on <NpcName>Sam</> for fresh fruit.

Text.SourceString: We plant a few vegetables and herbs, but our garden isn’t big enough to grow fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: We plant a few vegetables and herbs, but our garden isn’t big enough to grow fruit.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m not one for gardening, but it would be nice to rely less on <NpcName>Sam</> for fresh fruit.

Text.SourceString: We plant a few vegetables and herbs, but our garden isn’t big enough to grow fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: We plant a few vegetables and herbs, but our garden isn’t big enough to grow fruit.

Text.SourceString: It would be nice to have a big farm like yours. But then, taking care of it must be a big job.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be nice to have a big farm like yours. But then, taking care of it must be a big job.

Text.SourceString: Now that I think about it, I doubt I’d have the time for it.
Text.LocalizedString: Now that I think about it, I doubt I’d have the time for it.

Text.SourceString: I like to stretch my legs after work, and I usually end up at Fishensips.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to stretch my legs after work, and I usually end up at Fishensips.

Text.SourceString: Fun finds a way, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Fun finds a way, huh?

Text.SourceString: After school, I try to take <NpcName>Archie</> to the creek in the forest. I want to teach him things I learned in my childhood.
Text.LocalizedString: After school, I try to take <NpcName>Archie</> to the creek in the forest. I want to teach him things I learned in my childhood.

Text.SourceString: After school, I try to take <NpcName>Archie</> to the creek in the forest. I want to teach him things I learned in my childhood.
Text.LocalizedString: After school, I try to take <NpcName>Archie</> to the creek in the forest. I want to teach him things I learned in my childhood.

Text.SourceString: Where I’m from, there are plenty of small islands too. Just like here.
Text.LocalizedString: Where I’m from, there are plenty of small islands too. Just like here.

Text.SourceString: My nephew, <NpcName>Surya</>, is new in town. He studied the ocean, and he’s currently working for <NPCName>Ling</>.
Text.LocalizedString: My nephew, <NpcName>Surya</>, is new in town. He studied the ocean, and he’s currently working for <NPCName>Ling</>.

Text.SourceString: You’ve met him, right? He’s about your age, I believe.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ve met him, right? He’s about your age, I believe.

Text.SourceString: How’s the farm so far, <PlayerName>$player</>? You know, you can build a greenhouse on your farm to plant more crops. It’s not easy, but it would be worth it. You could grow anything in it year round.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s the farm so far, <PlayerName>$player</>? You know, you can build a greenhouse on your farm to plant more crops. It’s not easy, but it would be worth it. You could grow anything in it year round.

Text.SourceString: The soil here is very rich. When I take <NpcName>Archie</> to the forest, we always seem to stumble upon a new type of plant.
Text.LocalizedString: The soil here is very rich. When I take <NpcName>Archie</> to the forest, we always seem to stumble upon a new type of plant.

Text.SourceString: How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>? Things going okay on the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: How are you doing today, <PlayerName>$player</>? Things going okay on the farm?

Text.SourceString: I’m teaching <NpcName>Archie</> how to fish. The boy’s talented, but there’s definitely room for improvement.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m teaching <NpcName>Archie</> how to fish. The boy’s talented, but there’s definitely room for improvement.

Text.SourceString: My wife is a great cook. If she weren’t a carpenter, she’d probably be a chef. A big-name chef, I’m sure.
Text.LocalizedString: My wife is a great cook. If she weren’t a carpenter, she’d probably be a chef. A big-name chef, I’m sure.

Text.SourceString: I have no doubt that if she opened a restaurant, she’d have lots of loyal customers.//<portrait=happy>And one of them would be me. Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: I have no doubt that if she opened a restaurant, she’d have lots of loyal customers.//<portrait=happy>And one of them would be me. Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Dinda</> loves gardening, flower bouquets, salad, and pearls. I honestly don’t think she hates anything.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Dinda</> loves gardening, flower bouquets, salad, and pearls. I honestly don’t think she hates anything.

Text.SourceString: Oh! She hates avocados, ice cream, and mayonnaise.//Weird texture. To be frank, I’m no fan of mayonnaise either. It’s rather nasty.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! She hates avocados, ice cream, and mayonnaise.//Weird texture. To be frank, I’m no fan of mayonnaise either. It’s rather nasty.

Text.SourceString: This job comes with its hazards. I threw my back out one time and had to be on bed rest for the rest of the year.
Text.LocalizedString: This job comes with its hazards. I threw my back out one time and had to be on bed rest for the rest of the year.

Text.SourceString: I can still feel a bit of a pinch when I stretch in a particular position. Don’t worry, though. I’m fine, thanks.
Text.LocalizedString: I can still feel a bit of a pinch when I stretch in a particular position. Don’t worry, though. I’m fine, thanks.

Text.SourceString: We’re open till 5 pm today.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re open till 5 pm today.

Text.SourceString: Sunday is our short day. We’re only open until oneish.
Text.LocalizedString: Sunday is our short day. We’re only open until oneish.

Text.SourceString: There are some fascinating people on TV. Sometimes I’m at a loss for words.
Text.LocalizedString: There are some fascinating people on TV. Sometimes I’m at a loss for words.

Text.SourceString: I saw a grown man throw a bucketful of ice onto himself, outside, in Winter. Why?
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a grown man throw a bucketful of ice onto himself, outside, in Winter. Why?

Text.SourceString: You can make a bouquet of flowers yourself. You just need to get the instructions from <NpcName>Dinda</> or <NpcName>Ben</>. The key is to get to know them a little, and they’ll probably teach you.
Text.LocalizedString: You can make a bouquet of flowers yourself. You just need to get the instructions from <NpcName>Dinda</> or <NpcName>Ben</>. The key is to get to know them a little, and they’ll probably teach you.

Text.SourceString: A new day is here, and the birds are singing. What more could we ask for?
Text.LocalizedString: A new day is here, and the birds are singing. What more could we ask for?

Text.SourceString: Indeed. I did wake up in a very good mood. Why not?
Text.LocalizedString: Indeed. I did wake up in a very good mood. Why not?

Text.SourceString: The library is full of information. And you know what they say about knowledge!
Text.LocalizedString: The library is full of information. And you know what they say about knowledge!

Text.SourceString: That it’s a powerful thing!
Text.LocalizedString: That it’s a powerful thing!

Text.SourceString: How’s the farm so far, <PlayerName>$player</>? You know, you can build a greenhouse on your farm to plant more crops.//It’s not easy, but it would be worth it. You could grow anything in it year round.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s the farm so far, <PlayerName>$player</>? You know, you can build a greenhouse on your farm to plant more crops.//It’s not easy, but it would be worth it. You could grow anything in it year round.

Text.SourceString: Remember to take a rest, <PlayerName>$player</>. Wealth isn’t everything.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to take a rest, <PlayerName>$player</>. Wealth isn’t everything.

Text.SourceString: You’re always welcome to our house for dinner. I know it’s hard to be away from family sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re always welcome to our house for dinner. I know it’s hard to be away from family sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I like working outdoors when it isn’t raining.
Text.LocalizedString: I like working outdoors when it isn’t raining.

Text.SourceString: I get too busy during the week. I can only make it to yoga classes on Saturdays.
Text.LocalizedString: I get too busy during the week. I can only make it to yoga classes on Saturdays.

Text.SourceString: It’s not like they have yoga class any other day, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not like they have yoga class any other day, anyway.

Text.SourceString: My brother and I used to go fishing every day during Summer break. We’d disappear for the whole day, until sunset.
Text.LocalizedString: My brother and I used to go fishing every day during Summer break. We’d disappear for the whole day, until sunset.

Text.SourceString: Do you get your wood from the forest? I go there too because it’s close to the house.//There are plenty of places on the island to harvest wood, though, if you need more.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you get your wood from the forest? I go there too because it’s close to the house.//There are plenty of places on the island to harvest wood, though, if you need more.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie</> is fine, though he’ll go through periods of picky eating sometimes. But what kid doesn’t, right?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie</> is fine, though he’ll go through periods of picky eating sometimes. But what kid doesn’t, right?

Text.SourceString: We don’t sell our wood. We just don’t have the space to store that kind of inventory.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t sell our wood. We just don’t have the space to store that kind of inventory.

Text.SourceString: If you want to upgrade your cabin or build something, you need to supply the materials.
Text.LocalizedString: If you want to upgrade your cabin or build something, you need to supply the materials.

Text.LocalizedString: Do you get your wood from the forest? I go there too because it’s close to the house.//There are plenty of places on the island to harvest wood, though, if you need more.

Text.SourceString: It’s probably not the healthiest thing to cut wood indoors, with the sawdust flying around and all.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s probably not the healthiest thing to cut wood indoors, with the sawdust flying around and all.

Text.SourceString: I make it a habit to come to the town on weekends for some yoga.
Text.LocalizedString: I make it a habit to come to the town on weekends for some yoga.

Text.SourceString: Let’s face it, it’s an excellent excuse to see the islanders too.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s face it, it’s an excellent excuse to see the islanders too.

Text.LocalizedString: I get too busy during the week. I can only make it to yoga classes on Saturdays.

Text.SourceString: It’s probably not the healthiest thing to cut wood indoors, with the sawdust flying around and all.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s probably not the healthiest thing to cut wood indoors, with the sawdust flying around and all.

Text.SourceString: It’s best to do it outside and do the easy woodwork indoors.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s best to do it outside and do the easy woodwork indoors.

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking of taking <NpcName>Archie</> to the forest tomorrow after school.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking of taking <NpcName>Archie</> to the forest tomorrow after school.

Text.SourceString: The lake is too far from our house. I think by the time we went there to fish and came back, it would be close to midnight.
Text.LocalizedString: The lake is too far from our house. I think by the time we went there to fish and came back, it would be close to midnight.

Text.SourceString: Looking fresh there, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look like you got in some serious farming today.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking fresh there, <PlayerName>$player</>! You look like you got in some serious farming today.

Text.SourceString: I always feel good after a whole day of hard work. It’s great to feel productive!
Text.LocalizedString: I always feel good after a whole day of hard work. It’s great to feel productive!

Text.SourceString: My work requires me to have a lot of energy. So I make sure to start the day with a big breakfast every morning.
Text.LocalizedString: My work requires me to have a lot of energy. So I make sure to start the day with a big breakfast every morning.

Text.SourceString: You can see our available projects at the cash register. We keep the catalog there.
Text.LocalizedString: You can see our available projects at the cash register. We keep the catalog there.

Text.SourceString: You can buy the wall clocks if you like. They’re for sale.//Talk to <NpcName>Dinda</> for more information, though. She handles sales.
Text.LocalizedString: You can buy the wall clocks if you like. They’re for sale.//Talk to <NpcName>Dinda</> for more information, though. She handles sales.

Text.SourceString: It feels good to work with your hands, doesn’t it? You’re a farmer, <PlayerName>$player</>, you get it.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels good to work with your hands, doesn’t it? You’re a farmer, <PlayerName>$player</>, you get it.

Text.SourceString: We’re lucky, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not everyone can do what we do.//Don’t be too hard on yourself, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: We’re lucky, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not everyone can do what we do.//Don’t be too hard on yourself, okay?

Text.LocalizedString: My work requires me to have a lot of energy.//So I make sure to start the day with a big breakfast every morning.

Text.SourceString: I’m not trying to be difficult, but I can’t start working on a large project without payment.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not trying to be difficult, but I can’t start working on a large project without payment.

Text.SourceString: Well, large projects are more like upgrading a house or building a coop. I don’t consider making a shipping bin or a chair a large project.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, large projects are more like upgrading a house or building a coop. I don’t consider making a shipping bin or a chair a large project.

Text.SourceString: The thing with <NpcName>Archie</> is that if one of his friends is sick, the whole class will probably be sick. Then do you know who gets sick after that?
Text.LocalizedString: The thing with <NpcName>Archie</> is that if one of his friends is sick, the whole class will probably be sick. Then do you know who gets sick after that?

Text.SourceString: The parents, which includes me.
Text.LocalizedString: The parents, which includes me.

Text.SourceString: There’s so much we can pass on to our children. The little things we, the parents, do can become their habits.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so much we can pass on to our children. The little things we, the parents, do can become their habits.

Text.SourceString: There are simple craft projects you can make yourself to improve your farm.
Text.LocalizedString: There are simple craft projects you can make yourself to improve your farm.

Text.SourceString: We sell some blueprints if you’d like to try one.
Text.LocalizedString: We sell some blueprints if you’d like to try one.

Text.SourceString: The warmer weather is ahead. Are you planting any berries this Summer?
Text.LocalizedString: The warmer weather is ahead. Are you planting any berries this Summer?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Surya</> is my brother Suparmo’s oldest son.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Surya</> is my brother Suparmo’s oldest son.

Text.SourceString: He’s a smart one, you can just tell.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s a smart one, you can just tell.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to focus on work today and have a quiet evening with a plate of banana fritters.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to focus on work today and have a quiet evening with a plate of banana fritters.

Text.SourceString: I’ve spent a lot of time working outdoors this Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve spent a lot of time working outdoors this Summer.

Text.SourceString: As a farmer, you must spend a lot of your time outdoors too, I figure.//Well, at least for us, fresh air isn’t a problem. Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: As a farmer, you must spend a lot of your time outdoors too, I figure.//Well, at least for us, fresh air isn’t a problem. Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: The evenings have started to cool off a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: The evenings have started to cool off a bit.

Text.SourceString: I think the Fall weather is coming.
Text.LocalizedString: I think the Fall weather is coming.

Text.SourceString: It’s incredibly hot this year, I tell ya.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s incredibly hot this year, I tell ya.

Text.SourceString: It was much cooler last year.
Text.LocalizedString: It was much cooler last year.

Text.SourceString: Are you planting melons this year? It’s a popular fruit in our household.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you planting melons this year? It’s a popular fruit in our household.

Text.SourceString: I might go down to <NPCName>Sam</>’s and see if he’s got any melons.//You know, to score extra brownie points with <NpcName>Dinda</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I might go down to <NPCName>Sam</>’s and see if he’s got any melons.//You know, to score extra brownie points with <NpcName>Dinda</>.

Text.SourceString: What is it about Summer that makes people productive?//I woke up earlier than usual and got way more things done during the day.
Text.LocalizedString: What is it about Summer that makes people productive?//I woke up earlier than usual and got way more things done during the day.

Text.SourceString: I feel incredibly old now that I’ve started bragging about waking up early. Heh heh.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel incredibly old now that I’ve started bragging about waking up early. Heh heh.

Text.SourceString: I’m a bit busier than usual.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a bit busier than usual.

Text.SourceString: With the Harvest Festival coming up, I have to make sure all the booths are ready to use and fix the broken parts.
Text.LocalizedString: With the Harvest Festival coming up, I have to make sure all the booths are ready to use and fix the broken parts.

Text.SourceString: The mayor will have an empty booth for you to use if you decide to join in, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’ll make sure it’s nice and sturdy.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor will have an empty booth for you to use if you decide to join in, <PlayerName>$player</>. I’ll make sure it’s nice and sturdy.

Text.SourceString: I’m relieved the Harvest Festival ended without incident.//I’m always worried a booth might collapse or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m relieved the Harvest Festival ended without incident.//I’m always worried a booth might collapse or something.

Text.SourceString: I know it’s irrational, but I can’t help it sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it’s irrational, but I can’t help it sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I make sure to buy a few extra pumpkins for <NpcName>Archie</> and me to carve.//<portrait=happy>Now that the weather is nice, we just chill around the house and carve.
Text.LocalizedString: I make sure to buy a few extra pumpkins for <NpcName>Archie</> and me to carve.//<portrait=happy>Now that the weather is nice, we just chill around the house and carve.

Text.SourceString: I think this pumpkin carving thing will be a family tradition.//I can see it being passed down for generations.
Text.LocalizedString: I think this pumpkin carving thing will be a family tradition.//I can see it being passed down for generations.

Text.SourceString: To be frank, I don’t care much how our pumpkins look when I’m carving with <NpcName>Archie</>.//<portrait=happy>I just know it’s something he looks forward to every year, and it’s become a tradition.
Text.LocalizedString: To be frank, I don’t care much how our pumpkins look when I’m carving with <NpcName>Archie</>.//<portrait=happy>I just know it’s something he looks forward to every year, and it’s become a tradition.

Text.SourceString: Do you have a lot of pumpkins on your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have a lot of pumpkins on your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’m sure your farm looks excellent! I’ll have to go and see it sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sure your farm looks excellent! I’ll have to go and see it sometime.

Text.SourceString: One of these days, I’ll need to check on the community center and the lab to prepare them for Winter.//You know, just a quick inspection to make sure the heaters are working, the roofs aren’t leaking, and all that.
Text.LocalizedString: One of these days, I’ll need to check on the community center and the lab to prepare them for Winter.//You know, just a quick inspection to make sure the heaters are working, the roofs aren’t leaking, and all that.

Text.SourceString: Have you tried to make any crafts, like scarecrows? They can be very helpful on your farm.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried to make any crafts, like scarecrows? They can be very helpful on your farm.

Text.SourceString: I’m not going to focus much on work today. It’s cold, and I could use some downtime.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not going to focus much on work today. It’s cold, and I could use some downtime.

Text.SourceString: Our herb plants died. None of them can survive the Winter snow.
Text.LocalizedString: Our herb plants died. None of them can survive the Winter snow.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind working on projects in Winter. Keeping busy warms me up.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind working on projects in Winter. Keeping busy warms me up.

Text.SourceString: Sorry if I seem dusty. It’s not easy to get rid of sawdust.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry if I seem dusty. It’s not easy to get rid of sawdust.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I’m going to miss the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I’m going to miss the snow.

Text.SourceString: The snow may be melting soon, but the weather will still be chilly for at least a week.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow may be melting soon, but the weather will still be chilly for at least a week.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and I used to live in Indonesia. We fell in love with the quiet, peaceful life on the island!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and I used to live in Indonesia. We fell in love with the quiet, peaceful life on the island!

Text.SourceString: I still try to make it home every now and again to visit family.
Text.LocalizedString: I still try to make it home every now and again to visit family.

Text.SourceString: I can’t imagine a better life than working with my wife, <NPCName>Dinda</>.//<portrait=happy>She’s like my varnish – I’m just not complete without her.//<portrait=happy>Look at me, all <Italic>lovey-dovey</>! Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t imagine a better life than working with my wife, <NPCName>Dinda</>.//<portrait=happy>She’s like my varnish – I’m just not complete without her.//<portrait=happy>Look at me, all <Italic>lovey-dovey</>! Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, and <NPCName>Valentina</> get along really well!//<NPCName>Valentina</> is <NPCName>Rafael’s</> niece, you know. We see them all the time.
Text.LocalizedString: My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, and <NPCName>Valentina</> get along really well!//<NPCName>Valentina</> is <NPCName>Rafael’s</> niece, you know. We see them all the time.

Text.SourceString: I love watching them play together.
Text.LocalizedString: I love watching them play together.

Text.SourceString: People are so interesting, aren’t they? Everyone has a story!
Text.LocalizedString: People are so interesting, aren’t they? Everyone has a story!

Text.SourceString: Over the years, I’ve gotten really good at making chairs.
Text.LocalizedString: Over the years, I’ve gotten really good at making chairs.

Text.SourceString: My wife, <NPCName>Dinda</>, keeps a garden. It’s small, but the herbs she grows are delicious.
Text.LocalizedString: My wife, <NPCName>Dinda</>, keeps a garden. It’s small, but the herbs she grows are delicious.

Text.SourceString: If I were you, I’d hope she doesn’t expand.//<portrait=happy>She’d put you out of business!
Text.LocalizedString: If I were you, I’d hope she doesn’t expand.//<portrait=happy>She’d put you out of business!

Text.SourceString: I made a little table for <NPCName>Archie</> when he was a toddler.//He loved it!
Text.LocalizedString: I made a little table for <NPCName>Archie</> when he was a toddler.//He loved it!

Text.SourceString: We use it for storage now, but looking at it still brings back happy memories.
Text.LocalizedString: We use it for storage now, but looking at it still brings back happy memories.

Text.SourceString: I love stepping into the workshop in the morning. It’s my happy place.
Text.LocalizedString: I love stepping into the workshop in the morning. It’s my happy place.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and I actually knew each other in grade school! Can you believe it?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and I actually knew each other in grade school! Can you believe it?

Text.SourceString: I took <NPCName>Archie</> up to the old lighthouse last weekend.//<portrait=happy>He spent all his time looking for merfolk.//<portrait=annoyed>He didn’t see any.
Text.LocalizedString: I took <NPCName>Archie</> up to the old lighthouse last weekend.//<portrait=happy>He spent all his time looking for merfolk.//<portrait=annoyed>He didn’t see any.

Text.SourceString: If there’s one rule of woodworking, it’s this – respect the saw.
Text.LocalizedString: If there’s one rule of woodworking, it’s this – respect the saw.

Text.SourceString: See how I still have all my fingers? That’s because I take the rule seriously.
Text.LocalizedString: See how I still have all my fingers? That’s because I take the rule seriously.

Text.SourceString: Hey, there, <PlayerName>$player</>! Working hard or hardly working?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, there, <PlayerName>$player</>! Working hard or hardly working?

Text.SourceString: Working hard, I bet. Sorry, I didn’t mean to offend you.
Text.LocalizedString: Working hard, I bet. Sorry, I didn’t mean to offend you.

Text.SourceString: I always keep my tools handy. You’d be surprised how often you need a screwdriver.
Text.LocalizedString: I always keep my tools handy. You’d be surprised how often you need a screwdriver.

Text.SourceString: You must have quite the green thumb, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: You must have quite the green thumb, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: You should probably stop by the clinic to get that checked out.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! I crack me up.
Text.LocalizedString: You should probably stop by the clinic to get that checked out.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! I crack me up.

Text.SourceString: Can’t stop to talk today. Just got a huge order!
Text.LocalizedString: Can’t stop to talk today. Just got a huge order!

Text.SourceString: It’s from an independent video rental store on the mainland.//I know, how quaint! I think they still have movies on VHS.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s from an independent video rental store on the mainland.//I know, how quaint! I think they still have movies on VHS.

Text.SourceString: They want new shelving for their store, but the dimensions are odd.//A few centimeters under industry standard, rounded corners…
Text.LocalizedString: They want new shelving for their store, but the dimensions are odd.//A few centimeters under industry standard, rounded corners…

Text.SourceString: No problem for me, of course! I run a custom shop, you know, and I can make shelving to any specifications. It’s my passion.
Text.LocalizedString: No problem for me, of course! I run a custom shop, you know, and I can make shelving to any specifications. It’s my passion.

Text.SourceString: But like I said, can’t really talk today.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been woodworking ever since I was young.//I just did it for fun, but I never thought I could turn my hobby into a career.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been woodworking ever since I was young.//I just did it for fun, but I never thought I could turn my hobby into a career.

Text.SourceString: But people seem to love the work I do. I feel so blessed!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and I have been on Coral Island for…wow, has it been ten years already?//Gosh, must’ve been more!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and I have been on Coral Island for…wow, has it been ten years already?//Gosh, must’ve been more!

Text.SourceString: Time flies when you’re having fun!
Text.LocalizedString: Time flies when you’re having fun!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Bree</> and <NPCName>Walter</> are the other farmers in town.//They run the vineyard.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Bree</> and <NPCName>Walter</> are the other farmers in town.//They run the vineyard.

Text.SourceString: You should go introduce yourself if you haven’t already.
Text.LocalizedString: You should go introduce yourself if you haven’t already.

Text.SourceString: You’re a busy little bee, aren’t you? Well, don’t let me get in your way!
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a busy little bee, aren’t you? Well, don’t let me get in your way!

Text.SourceString: Have you met my nephew yet? <NPCName>Surya</>? He’s a lovely fellow!//You should stop by the lab and say hello.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you met my nephew yet? <NPCName>Surya</>? He’s a lovely fellow!//You should stop by the lab and say hello.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Rafael Sanchez</> doesn’t talk much, but he doesn’t have to.//<portrait=normal>His craftsmanship speaks for him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Rafael Sanchez</> doesn’t talk much, but he doesn’t have to.//<portrait=normal>His craftsmanship speaks for him.

Text.SourceString: I’m a woodworker, but people tend to think of me as a general handyman too.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a woodworker, but people tend to think of me as a general handyman too.

Text.SourceString: That’s okay. I love to help out!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s okay. I love to help out!

Text.SourceString: Ever tried a yoga class with <NPCName>Leah</>? I love it! She’s a wonderful instructor.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever tried a yoga class with <NPCName>Leah</>? I love it! She’s a wonderful instructor.

Text.SourceString: You should join us in class sometime, <PlayerName>$player</>! You’d love it.
Text.LocalizedString: You should join us in class sometime, <PlayerName>$player</>! You’d love it.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been learning so much about marine life ever since my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, moved in with us.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been learning so much about marine life ever since my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, moved in with us.

Text.SourceString: Like, did you know octopuses have three hearts? Fascinating stuff!
Text.LocalizedString: Like, did you know octopuses have three hearts? Fascinating stuff!

Text.SourceString: When my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, moved to town, I invited him to come live with us right away.
Text.LocalizedString: When my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, moved to town, I invited him to come live with us right away.

Text.SourceString: He was hesitant at first, but I wouldn’t take no for an answer! He’s family.
Text.LocalizedString: He was hesitant at first, but I wouldn’t take no for an answer! He’s family.

Text.SourceString: He’s also a great addition to family board game night. So, win-win!
Text.LocalizedString: He’s also a great addition to family board game night. So, win-win!

Text.SourceString: If <NPCName>Kira</> looks intimidating, it’s because she is.
Text.LocalizedString: If <NPCName>Kira</> looks intimidating, it’s because she is.

Text.SourceString: Don’t let her prickly demeanor fool you, though. She’s a good person at heart.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t let her prickly demeanor fool you, though. She’s a good person at heart.

Text.SourceString: I love the smell of sawdust in the morning!
Text.LocalizedString: I love the smell of sawdust in the morning!

Text.SourceString: You’re not really in a talking mood today, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I can tell. I have a sixth sense about these things.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not really in a talking mood today, are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I can tell. I have a sixth sense about these things.

Text.SourceString: I’ll tell you the same thing I tell my son, <NPCName>Archie</>. Measure twice, cut once.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll tell you the same thing I tell my son, <NPCName>Archie</>. Measure twice, cut once.

Text.SourceString: Like it? I made it up myself!
Text.LocalizedString: Like it? I made it up myself!

Text.SourceString: Work is really picking up! I wonder if I’ll need to expand.
Text.LocalizedString: Work is really picking up! I wonder if I’ll need to expand.

Text.SourceString: My favorite day of the year is Beach Cleanup Day. Coral Island is beautiful, but it takes work to keep it that way!
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite day of the year is Beach Cleanup Day. Coral Island is beautiful, but it takes work to keep it that way!

Text.SourceString: You’re coming this year, right?
Text.LocalizedString: You’re coming this year, right?

Text.SourceString: Do you know <NPCName>Bree</> from the vineyard yet? I heard she used to be a model.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know <NPCName>Bree</> from the vineyard yet? I heard she used to be a model.

Text.SourceString: She still is, of course.//<portrait=happy>A model citizen, that is!
Text.LocalizedString: She still is, of course.//<portrait=happy>A model citizen, that is!

Text.SourceString: I saw a wonderfully crafted banister at the vineyard the other day.//Rich mahogany, exquisite inlays, beautiful curves.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a wonderfully crafted banister at the vineyard the other day.//Rich mahogany, exquisite inlays, beautiful curves.

Text.SourceString: I’m a man who appreciates a fine banister.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a man who appreciates a fine banister.

Text.SourceString: Did you know there are over seventeen species of trees growing on Coral Island?//<portrait=happy>Well, now you do!
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know there are over seventeen species of trees growing on Coral Island?//<portrait=happy>Well, now you do!

Text.SourceString: Have you met <NPCName>Zarah</> yet? She’s very mysterious, always coming and going!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you met <NPCName>Zarah</> yet? She’s very mysterious, always coming and going!

Text.SourceString: Y’know, it’s not just wood that I work with. I also carve a mean jack-o’-lantern.
Text.LocalizedString: Y’know, it’s not just wood that I work with. I also carve a mean jack-o’-lantern.

Text.SourceString: I’ve never been diving in the ocean before, but my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, goes all the time. He tells me it’s beautiful down there.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve never been diving in the ocean before, but my nephew, <NPCName>Surya</>, goes all the time. He tells me it’s beautiful down there.

Text.SourceString: I really need to find the time someday.
Text.LocalizedString: I really need to find the time someday.

Text.SourceString: My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, has been pretending to be a squirrel for the past few weeks.
Text.LocalizedString: My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, has been pretending to be a squirrel for the past few weeks.

Text.SourceString: He’s actually very convincing. The only problem is I keep finding nuts hidden around the house.//<portrait=normal>He sure loves animals, that one.
Text.LocalizedString: He’s actually very convincing. The only problem is I keep finding nuts hidden around the house.//<portrait=normal>He sure loves animals, that one.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Surya</> said there are whales not too far from here! I’d love to see them one day.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Surya</> said there are whales not too far from here! I’d love to see them one day.

Text.SourceString: I used to make fanciful artisan pieces.//<portrait=happy>Bookshelves with intricate scrollwork or handmade jigsaw puzzles.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to make fanciful artisan pieces.//<portrait=happy>Bookshelves with intricate scrollwork or handmade jigsaw puzzles.

Text.SourceString: Now I mostly make utilitarian pieces. Desks, tables, chairs. No frills, just practical.
Text.LocalizedString: Now I mostly make utilitarian pieces. Desks, tables, chairs. No frills, just practical.

Text.SourceString: I enjoy those too, but sometimes I miss the old days.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy those too, but sometimes I miss the old days.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting into chess! I started playing with <NPCName>Yuri</> at the shack, and it’s really grown on me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting into chess! I started playing with <NPCName>Yuri</> at the shack, and it’s really grown on me.

Text.SourceString: I might make her a custom chessboard as a thank-you. Don’t tell her, though. I want it to be a surprise!
Text.LocalizedString: I might make her a custom chessboard as a thank-you. Don’t tell her, though. I want it to be a surprise!

Text.SourceString: I’d love to teach <NPCName>Archie</> more about woodworking.//But he seems to want to be a vet when he grows up, which is fine by me.//He should follow his heart.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d love to teach <NPCName>Archie</> more about woodworking.//But he seems to want to be a vet when he grows up, which is fine by me.//He should follow his heart.

Text.SourceString: I’m feeling a little under the weather today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m feeling a little under the weather today.

Text.SourceString: Whenever I start feeling sick, <NPCName>Dinda</> makes me tea with fresh peppermint from her garden.//It peps me right up!
Text.LocalizedString: Whenever I start feeling sick, <NPCName>Dinda</> makes me tea with fresh peppermint from her garden.//It peps me right up!

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking of hiring <NPCName>Macy</> to take a family portrait.//<portrait=normal>She’s an excellent photographer!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking of hiring <NPCName>Macy</> to take a family portrait.//<portrait=normal>She’s an excellent photographer!

Text.SourceString: How’s the soil today, <PlayerName>$player</>? Nutrient rich, I hope!
Text.LocalizedString: How’s the soil today, <PlayerName>$player</>? Nutrient rich, I hope!

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Jack</> in yoga class last week!//He’s surprisingly flexible.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Jack</> in yoga class last week!//He’s surprisingly flexible.

Text.SourceString: What you heard is true.<NPCName>Kira</> doesn’t celebrate birthdays.//I think <NPCName>Kenny</> does, though.
Text.LocalizedString: What you heard is true.<NPCName>Kira</> doesn’t celebrate birthdays.//I think <NPCName>Kenny</> does, though.

Text.SourceString: No, I don’t know when <NPCName>Kenny’s</> birthday is. Sorry!
Text.LocalizedString: No, I don’t know when <NPCName>Kenny’s</> birthday is. Sorry!

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking about taking up calligraphy. You know, with all my spare time…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking about taking up calligraphy. You know, with all my spare time…

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Theo</> is one of the most positive people I know. I’m not sure how he does it, given–
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Theo</> is one of the most positive people I know. I’m not sure how he does it, given–

Text.SourceString: Well, it doesn’t matter. He’s a remarkable person.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, it doesn’t matter. He’s a remarkable person.

Text.SourceString: My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, is a huge animal lover. He’s always watching the animal channel on TV, learning all sorts of interesting facts.
Text.LocalizedString: My son, <NPCName>Archie</>, is a huge animal lover. He’s always watching the animal channel on TV, learning all sorts of interesting facts.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> has <NPCName>Dinda’s</> empathetic personality, that’s for sure.//He’d make a great vet.//Umm, nope.//<portrait=happy>He <Italic>will</> make a great vet.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> has <NPCName>Dinda’s</> empathetic personality, that’s for sure.//He’d make a great vet.//Umm, nope.//<portrait=happy>He <Italic>will</> make a great vet.

Text.SourceString: I almost sawed through my wallet in my workshop earlier today!//That’s never happened before.
Text.LocalizedString: I almost sawed through my wallet in my workshop earlier today!//That’s never happened before.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Jim</> doing some kind of martial arts thing at the beach the other day.//Karate, maybe. It was interesting!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Jim</> doing some kind of martial arts thing at the beach the other day.//Karate, maybe. It was interesting!

Text.SourceString: I was going to ask him about it, but he looked like he wanted to be left alone.
Text.LocalizedString: I was going to ask him about it, but he looked like he wanted to be left alone.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> surprised me with a beautiful bouquet of wooden flowers the other day.//<portrait=normal>She made them herself!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> surprised me with a beautiful bouquet of wooden flowers the other day.//<portrait=normal>She made them herself!

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how she found the time to make them without me knowing.//She’s so sweet! And sneaky!
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how she found the time to make them without me knowing.//She’s so sweet! And sneaky!

Text.SourceString: We just harvested some fresh herbs from <NPCName>Dinda’s</> garden!
Text.LocalizedString: We just harvested some fresh herbs from <NPCName>Dinda’s</> garden!

Text.SourceString: Let me tell ya, there’s nothing like fresh produce.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell ya, there’s nothing like fresh produce.

Text.SourceString: But look who I’m talking to! I don’t need to tell you that, do I?
Text.LocalizedString: But look who I’m talking to! I don’t need to tell you that, do I?

Text.SourceString: Have you checked out the Fall colors yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you checked out the Fall colors yet?

Text.SourceString: I love this time of year. The air is crisp, the leaves put on a beautiful show…
Text.LocalizedString: I love this time of year. The air is crisp, the leaves put on a beautiful show…

Text.SourceString: And when the leaves fall off, you can really see how much yield a tree will give. It’s gorgeous!
Text.LocalizedString: And when the leaves fall off, you can really see how much yield a tree will give. It’s gorgeous!

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing better than sitting with a cup of hot cocoa while looking at the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing better than sitting with a cup of hot cocoa while looking at the snow.

Text.SourceString: I love watching the snow fall!//<portrait=concerned>From inside, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: I love watching the snow fall!//<portrait=concerned>From inside, of course.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been racking my brain, trying to think of what to get <NPCName>Dinda</> for her birthday.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been racking my brain, trying to think of what to get <NPCName>Dinda</> for her birthday.

Text.SourceString: Oh, it’s not for a while yet. But I’m terrible at coming up with gift ideas. This year, I want to be prepared!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it’s not for a while yet. But I’m terrible at coming up with gift ideas. This year, I want to be prepared!

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival is just around the corner!
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival is just around the corner!

Text.SourceString: Hot enough for ya? ’Cause it sure is for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot enough for ya? ’Cause it sure is for me.

Text.SourceString: There are simple craft projects you can make yourself to improve your farm, like scarecrows or lampposts.
Text.LocalizedString: There are simple craft projects you can make yourself to improve your farm, like scarecrows or lampposts.

Text.SourceString: We sell some blueprints if you’d like to try one.
Text.LocalizedString: We sell some blueprints if you’d like to try one.

Text.SourceString: I might go to the forest tomorrow and get some more wood.
Text.LocalizedString: I might go to the forest tomorrow and get some more wood.

Text.SourceString: We’re making some new furniture.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re making some new furniture.

Text.SourceString: I thought I’d stretch a bit here.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought I’d stretch a bit here.

Text.SourceString: The house isn’t bad, eh? <NpcName>Dinda</> and I built it ourselves. Took us a long time, but it’s really sturdy!//We never thought we needed to expand, because we were too caught up in work.
Text.LocalizedString: The house isn’t bad, eh? <NpcName>Dinda</> and I built it ourselves. Took us a long time, but it’s really sturdy!//We never thought we needed to expand, because we were too caught up in work.

Text.SourceString: We used to live in what’s now the workshop, behind the shop counter, until we wanted to enlarge our family.//Then we built the addition with extra bedrooms.
Text.LocalizedString: We used to live in what’s now the workshop, behind the shop counter, until we wanted to enlarge our family.//Then we built the addition with extra bedrooms.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ll go back to work today. I’ll just relax and see my friends.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ll go back to work today. I’ll just relax and see my friends.

Text.SourceString: Sorry if I seem dusty. It’s not easy to get rid of sawdust.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry if I seem dusty. It’s not easy to get rid of sawdust.

Text.SourceString: Taking a break, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Taking a break, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’m sure <NpcName>Rafael</> and <NpcName>Pablo</> are the only blacksmiths around here. They’re the only ones who have the equipment to upgrade tools.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sure <NpcName>Rafael</> and <NpcName>Pablo</> are the only blacksmiths around here. They’re the only ones who have the equipment to upgrade tools.

Text.SourceString: It’s probably not the worst idea to carry a sword or something when you go to the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s probably not the worst idea to carry a sword or something when you go to the cavern.

Text.SourceString: I think this place should have a trivia night. Don’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: I think this place should have a trivia night. Don’t you?

Text.SourceString: I like teaching <NPCName>Archie</> fishing.//It’s a good skill to have.
Text.LocalizedString: I like teaching <NPCName>Archie</> fishing.//It’s a good skill to have.

Text.SourceString: It’s quiet here. So peaceful. One of my favorite places for sure.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s quiet here. So peaceful. One of my favorite places for sure.

Text.SourceString: Hardwood is great to work with. I find a ton down in the deep forest.
Text.LocalizedString: Hardwood is great to work with. I find a ton down in the deep forest.

Text.SourceString: I really should reorganize my workshop. But I’m always just so busy.
Text.LocalizedString: I really should reorganize my workshop. But I’m always just so busy.

Text.SourceString: You can hear the wind whistling through the trees from here.
Text.LocalizedString: You can hear the wind whistling through the trees from here.

Text.SourceString: When I walked into the workshop this morning, there was this amazing sunbeam streaming through the window.
Text.LocalizedString: When I walked into the workshop this morning, there was this amazing sunbeam streaming through the window.

Text.SourceString: The way it caught yesterday’s sawdust floating through the air was just… It was just magical.
Text.LocalizedString: The way it caught yesterday’s sawdust floating through the air was just… It was just magical.

Text.SourceString: I must have watched it for fifteen minutes.

Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Surya</> loves working with <NPCName>Ling</> in the lab.

Text.SourceString: Wow! You’re out and about!//I think I’ll stay indoors today because, you know…the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow! You’re out and about!//I think I’ll stay indoors today because, you know…the rain.

Text.SourceString: My mom liked to make a dish with bamboo shoots. Where I’m from, bamboo shoots are easy to find. They’re everywhere!//I used to eat it almost every day. Got tired of it. The smell turns my stomach.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom liked to make a dish with bamboo shoots. Where I’m from, bamboo shoots are easy to find. They’re everywhere!//I used to eat it almost every day. Got tired of it. The smell turns my stomach.

Text.SourceString: I can almost smell it right now. Ugh…//Feels like I got some stuck in my nose. Blech!
Text.LocalizedString: I can almost smell it right now. Ugh…//Feels like I got some stuck in my nose. Blech!

Text.SourceString: We have glass in our inventory for making windows.//<portrait=happy>Do you need any windows?
Text.LocalizedString: We have glass in our inventory for making windows.//<portrait=happy>Do you need any windows?

Text.SourceString: There isn’t a better time to get windows installed than Summer.//<portrait=happy>Imagine this, a hot evening…you open the windows…and fall asleep in a nice breeze. Huh?
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t a better time to get windows installed than Summer.//<portrait=happy>Imagine this, a hot evening…you open the windows…and fall asleep in a nice breeze. Huh?

Text.SourceString: We have glass in our inventory for making windows.//<portrait=happy>Do you need any windows?
Text.LocalizedString: We have glass in our inventory for making windows.//<portrait=happy>Do you need any windows?

Text.SourceString: There isn’t a better time to get windows installed than Winter.//<portrait=happy>Imagine this, an ice-cold evening…you close the windows…and fall asleep in a warm, toasty room. Huh?
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t a better time to get windows installed than Winter.//<portrait=happy>Imagine this, an ice-cold evening…you close the windows…and fall asleep in a warm, toasty room. Huh?

Text.SourceString: I heard from <NpcName>Rafael</> that the cemetery has been extra moldy lately.//Must be from all the snow last week.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard from <NpcName>Rafael</> that the cemetery has been extra moldy lately.//Must be from all the snow last week.

Text.SourceString: I like staining wood more than making furniture.
Text.LocalizedString: I like staining wood more than making furniture.

Text.SourceString: Something about gliding the color on the wood… So satisfying!
Text.LocalizedString: Something about gliding the color on the wood… So satisfying!

Text.SourceString: I had some bad yogurt the other day. I knew it was kind of bad when I ate it. Halfway in, I realized it tasted funny.//But I didn’t listen to myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I had some bad yogurt the other day. I knew it was kind of bad when I ate it. Halfway in, I realized it tasted funny.//But I didn’t listen to myself.

Text.SourceString: I finished the whole jar, and now I’m paying for it.
Text.LocalizedString: I finished the whole jar, and now I’m paying for it.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NpcName>Archie</> is missing out on something, being an only child and all, you know.//I grew up with a sibling. Even now, in our old age, we stick together like peanut butter to the roof of your mouth.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NpcName>Archie</> is missing out on something, being an only child and all, you know.//I grew up with a sibling. Even now, in our old age, we stick together like peanut butter to the roof of your mouth.

Text.SourceString: When my brother and I were little kids, we had a lot of fun together.//The bond is different with siblings. I’m afraid I’m depriving <NpcName>Archie</> of that.
Text.LocalizedString: When my brother and I were little kids, we had a lot of fun together.//The bond is different with siblings. I’m afraid I’m depriving <NpcName>Archie</> of that.

Text.SourceString: I can see <NpcName>Archie</> growing up to be like <NpcName>Zarah</>. Always on the go. An adventurer.//I think as long as I teach him all the skills I have, he’ll do fine.
Text.LocalizedString: I can see <NpcName>Archie</> growing up to be like <NpcName>Zarah</>. Always on the go. An adventurer.//I think as long as I teach him all the skills I have, he’ll do fine.

Text.SourceString: I have no doubt <NpcName>Archie</> will learn more skills as he grows older.
Text.LocalizedString: I have no doubt <NpcName>Archie</> will learn more skills as he grows older.

Text.SourceString: I get worried a lot, thinking about <NpcName>Archie</> in the forest somewhere, alone, hurt.
Text.LocalizedString: I get worried a lot, thinking about <NpcName>Archie</> in the forest somewhere, alone, hurt.

Text.SourceString: But I don’t want to hold him back just for my peace of mind.//Hardest thing about being a parent.
Text.LocalizedString: But I don’t want to hold him back just for my peace of mind.//Hardest thing about being a parent.

Text.SourceString: Oh, <NpcName>Luke</>? Yes, I have some stories about him.//<portrait=normal>I’ve known his parents since before he was born. <NpcName>Dinda</> and I watched <NpcName>Luke</> grow up in our backyard.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, <NpcName>Luke</>? Yes, I have some stories about him.//<portrait=normal>I’ve known his parents since before he was born. <NpcName>Dinda</> and I watched <NpcName>Luke</> grow up in our backyard.

Text.SourceString: I remember thinking, “Wow! What a polite and thoughtful young man.” I taught him how to fish in the creek.//<portrait=normal>This was all before <NpcName>Archie</> was born. How time flies, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: I remember thinking, “Wow! What a polite and thoughtful young man.” I taught him how to fish in the creek.//<portrait=normal>This was all before <NpcName>Archie</> was born. How time flies, eh?

Text.SourceString: I used to take <NpcName>Luke</> fishing by the pier. We’d hunt for bait and spend the whole day at the beach.//<portrait=happy>That kid turned red like a banana bruises. Very fast!
Text.LocalizedString: I used to take <NpcName>Luke</> fishing by the pier. We’d hunt for bait and spend the whole day at the beach.//<portrait=happy>That kid turned red like a banana bruises. Very fast!

Text.SourceString: I’m kind of an expert at pumpkin carving, if I say so myself.//Not to brag, but I’ve been doing it since…oh boy!//<portrait=normal>Since before <NpcName>Archie</> was born. Taught young <NpcName>Luke</>. That was me!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m kind of an expert at pumpkin carving, if I say so myself.//Not to brag, but I’ve been doing it since…oh boy!//<portrait=normal>Since before <NpcName>Archie</> was born. Taught young <NpcName>Luke</>. That was me!

Text.SourceString: I work outdoors and go to the forest a lot.//It’s better if I wear long pants. I don’t want to get all kinds of bug bites on my legs from wearing shorts for fashion.
Text.LocalizedString: I work outdoors and go to the forest a lot.//It’s better if I wear long pants. I don’t want to get all kinds of bug bites on my legs from wearing shorts for fashion.

Text.SourceString: I work outdoors and go to the forest a lot.//It’s better if I wear long pants, but in this heat? No. No can do! That’s what I say.
Text.LocalizedString: I work outdoors and go to the forest a lot.//It’s better if I wear long pants, but in this heat? No. No can do! That’s what I say.

Text.SourceString: If you’re decorating, we make handcrafted knickknacks and furniture.
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re decorating, we make handcrafted knickknacks and furniture.

Text.SourceString: Don’t get too close. Sawdust everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t get too close. Sawdust everywhere.

Text.SourceString: You can talk to <NpcName>Dinda</> if you need something built.//She should be inside.
Text.LocalizedString: You can talk to <NpcName>Dinda</> if you need something built.//She should be inside.

Text.SourceString: I built that little garden over there for <NpcName>Dinda</>.//<portrait=happy>An anniversary gift. Looks pretty solid, right? It hangs great too.
Text.LocalizedString: I built that little garden over there for <NpcName>Dinda</>.//<portrait=happy>An anniversary gift. Looks pretty solid, right? It hangs great too.

Text.SourceString: Taking a stroll, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Taking a stroll, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I have to pick up a tool from <NpcName>Rafael</> tomorrow. Hopefully, he’s around.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to pick up a tool from <NpcName>Rafael</> tomorrow. Hopefully, he’s around.

Text.SourceString: I had to throw out an old bookshelf the other day.//A client asked me to fix it for him, but it was totally infested with termites.
Text.LocalizedString: I had to throw out an old bookshelf the other day.//A client asked me to fix it for him, but it was totally infested with termites.

Text.SourceString: I put it out on the street for just a minute, but when I came back, it was gone! Didn’t even have the chance to take it over to the recycling center.//<portrait=concerned>And later, I could have sworn I saw it outside <NPCName>Ben’s</> caravan.//Should I warn him about the termites? I think maybe I should.
Text.LocalizedString: I put it out on the street for just a minute, but when I came back, it was gone! Didn’t even have the chance to take it over to the recycling center.//<portrait=concerned>And later, I could have sworn I saw it outside <NPCName>Ben’s</> caravan.//Should I warn him about the termites? I think maybe I should.

Text.SourceString: I’ve always dreamed of being a lumberjack.//You know, spending the day in the woods, wearing one of those red flannel shirts.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve always dreamed of being a lumberjack.//You know, spending the day in the woods, wearing one of those red flannel shirts.

Text.SourceString: But it’s hard work, chopping down trees all day. I think it’s actually just the flannel I like.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s hard work, chopping down trees all day. I think it’s actually just the flannel I like.

Text.SourceString: I used to love climbing trees as a kid. Now, I guess I just cut them down.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to love climbing trees as a kid. Now, I guess I just cut them down.

Text.SourceString: There’s something sad about that, isn’t there?//<portrait=normal>Well, best not to think about it!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something sad about that, isn’t there?//<portrait=normal>Well, best not to think about it!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda’s</> always growing something in her herb garden!//<portrait=concerned>But between you and me, it’s mostly mint.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda’s</> always growing something in her herb garden!//<portrait=concerned>But between you and me, it’s mostly mint.

Text.SourceString: I used to whittle away hours in a forest just like this.//<portrait=happy>No, literally. I’d sit with my whittling knife for hours, carving fallen sticks into unicorns, chess pieces, you name it.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to whittle away hours in a forest just like this.//<portrait=happy>No, literally. I’d sit with my whittling knife for hours, carving fallen sticks into unicorns, chess pieces, you name it.

Text.SourceString: I still try to get out to the forest to whittle if I can.//The shop’s just so busy these days it’s hard to find the time.
Text.LocalizedString: I still try to get out to the forest to whittle if I can.//The shop’s just so busy these days it’s hard to find the time.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been browsing TVs down at the electronics store lately.//I think it’s time for an upgrade.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been browsing TVs down at the electronics store lately.//I think it’s time for an upgrade.

Text.SourceString: I love the water, but I try not to go to that strange temple on the other side of the island.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the water, but I try not to go to that strange temple on the other side of the island.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a superstitious man, but something about that place just spooks me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a superstitious man, but something about that place just spooks me.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I think about hiring an extra hand down at the shop.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I think about hiring an extra hand down at the shop.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know, though. There’s something special about keeping it in the family.//Maybe I can reach out to more cousins to work there.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know, though. There’s something special about keeping it in the family.//Maybe I can reach out to more cousins to work there.

Text.SourceString: I tried to give <NPCName>Dinda’s</> nose a bop the other day, but I missed and bopped her eye instead.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to give <NPCName>Dinda’s</> nose a bop the other day, but I missed and bopped her eye instead.

Text.SourceString: That’s like the worst possible place to bop.//Anyway, we spent the day at the clinic. She’s okay.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s like the worst possible place to bop.//Anyway, we spent the day at the clinic. She’s okay.

Text.SourceString: I think <NPCName>Surya</> still gets lost in the forest sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I think <NPCName>Surya</> still gets lost in the forest sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think he knows I know.//But I know.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think he knows I know.//But I know.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NPCName>Archie</> watching a grasshopper the other day. He watched it for over an hour.//<portrait=annoyed>Kids, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NPCName>Archie</> watching a grasshopper the other day. He watched it for over an hour.//<portrait=annoyed>Kids, huh?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie’s</> been asking us to get a pet ferret. I’m running out of ways to say no.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie’s</> been asking us to get a pet ferret. I’m running out of ways to say no.

Text.SourceString: I want you to know how much I appreciate you as a friend, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I want you to know how much I appreciate you as a friend, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: You’re reliable, dependable.//Exactly the sort of person I like to be around.//<portrait=normal>I guess what I’m saying is I’d be happy to write you a recommendation letter.//You know. If it ever comes up.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re reliable, dependable.//Exactly the sort of person I like to be around.//<portrait=normal>I guess what I’m saying is I’d be happy to write you a recommendation letter.//You know. If it ever comes up.

Text.SourceString: I saw a Pufferfish lobbyist at the beach cleanup the other day. I can’t believe the nerve of those…those…
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a Pufferfish lobbyist at the beach cleanup the other day. I can’t believe the nerve of those…those…

Text.SourceString: As if they cared about the environment!//<portrait=annoyed>As if they cared about the welfare of our town! Hypocrites! They want to destroy this place!//I was so mad I almost walked out.
Text.LocalizedString: As if they cared about the environment!//<portrait=annoyed>As if they cared about the welfare of our town! Hypocrites! They want to destroy this place!//I was so mad I almost walked out.

Text.SourceString: I’m thinking about surprising <NPCName>Dinda</> with a second honeymoon soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking about surprising <NPCName>Dinda</> with a second honeymoon soon.

Text.SourceString: I was trying to plan the perfect place to take her, but then I remembered she loves spontaneity.//So, I think the best plan might be to just go to the port and decide when we’re there!
Text.LocalizedString: I was trying to plan the perfect place to take her, but then I remembered she loves spontaneity.//So, I think the best plan might be to just go to the port and decide when we’re there!

Text.SourceString: You know, I’m starting to realize <NPCName>Archie</> may not want to pursue woodworking like his old man.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I’m starting to realize <NPCName>Archie</> may not want to pursue woodworking like his old man.

Text.SourceString: It breaks my heart more than a little.//But the boy’s got to pursue his dreams, right? I want to encourage that.
Text.LocalizedString: It breaks my heart more than a little.//But the boy’s got to pursue his dreams, right? I want to encourage that.

Text.SourceString: My workshop is a total mess!//<portrait=happy>Just the way I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: My workshop is a total mess!//<portrait=happy>Just the way I like it.

Text.SourceString: We have some iced tea in the fridge if you’re thirsty.//Help yourself.
Text.LocalizedString: We have some iced tea in the fridge if you’re thirsty.//Help yourself.

Text.SourceString: I was going to make <NPCName>Yuri</> a custom chess set as a thank-you for introducing me to the game, but she keeps beating me!
Text.LocalizedString: I was going to make <NPCName>Yuri</> a custom chess set as a thank-you for introducing me to the game, but she keeps beating me!

Text.SourceString: I’m still planning to, but I sure wish I could win a game once in a while.//<portrait=happy>Say, we should play sometime!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still planning to, but I sure wish I could win a game once in a while.//<portrait=happy>Say, we should play sometime!

Text.SourceString: I need to start thinking about an anniversary present soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to start thinking about an anniversary present soon.

Text.SourceString: No woodcraft pieces. <NPCName>Dinda</> and I have done too many of those for each other over the years.//<portrait=happy>Instead, I think I’ll get her an air fryer. She’ll love it!//<portrait=concerned>Well…maybe I’ll keep thinking.
Text.LocalizedString: No woodcraft pieces. <NPCName>Dinda</> and I have done too many of those for each other over the years.//<portrait=happy>Instead, I think I’ll get her an air fryer. She’ll love it!//<portrait=concerned>Well…maybe I’ll keep thinking.

Text.SourceString: I’m so happy now I’ve started being more selective with my work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so happy now I’ve started being more selective with my work.

Text.SourceString: I turned down five more jobs the other day. I’ve never felt so free!
Text.LocalizedString: I turned down five more jobs the other day. I’ve never felt so free!
